# Internationalization (required)

- **Never** introduce new user-visible English (or any fixed locale) as raw JSX text or string literals inside JSX in `src/**/*.tsx`, except under ignored paths below.
- **Always** use `useTranslation` + `t('…')` (or `Trans`). Add keys to `src/i18n/locales/en/<namespace>.json` first; extend `fr`, `de`, etc. when the task involves those languages.
- **Ignored for this rule:** `src/components/ui/**`, `**/*.test.tsx`, `**/__tests__/**`, `tests/**`, `src/pages/legal/**`.
- ESLint **`i18n/no-raw-jsx-text`** enforces this; fix warnings rather than disabling unless there is a documented exception.

**Full playbook** (repo map, security, workflow, anti-patterns): **`AGENTS.md`** in this folder — not only i18n.
